# Cloud Supabase credentials for the data migration runbook (docs/06_data_migration.md).
#
# Copy this file to .env.cloud (which is gitignored) and fill in the real values.
# Used only by your dev workstation when running the migration heredocs — the
# values are forwarded over SSH to the VM and never written to its disk.

# Full Postgres connection string for the cloud Supabase project.
#
# Where to get it:
#   Supabase dashboard → Settings → Database → Connection string → URI tab
#   → toggle to "Session pooler"
#   (NOT "Direct connection" — that hostname is IPv6-only and almost
#    certainly unreachable from a typical Proxmox / home-LAN VM.
#    NOT "Transaction pooler" port 6543 — it doesn't support the
#    session-level state pg_dump requires.)
#
# Replace [YOUR-PASSWORD] in the copied URI with your actual database password
# (the one from "Database password" on the same dashboard page).
#
# Example shape (yours will differ in region and ref):
#   postgresql://postgres.xyzabcdefghij:your-real-pw@aws-0-eu-west-2.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
CLOUD_DB_URL=

# Optional: space-separated list of non-public schemas to include in the dump.
# Leave empty unless you've added schemas like "reporting" or "analytics" on cloud.
EXTRA_SCHEMAS=

# Optional: space-separated list of representative tables for the row-count
# verification step. Pick 3–5 of your largest user-data tables.
TABLES="public.profiles public.orders auth.users"
